{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_lxy6skgdwzo7uh27b5qt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"275810111","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/private/tmp/tokenwarden-bench/claude-code/2026-07-20T20-12-48-884Z/tokenwarden-docs-from-code-3/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md","content":"# Cache API\n\nThe Cache API provides a simple in-memory caching mechanism using a `Map`-based storage.\n\n## createCache()\n\nCreates and returns a new cache instance with basic CRUD operations.\n\n```javascript\nconst cache = createCache()\n```\n\nReturns an object with the following methods: `get`, `set`, `delete`, and `clear`.\n\n## Methods\n\n### get(key)\n\nRetrieves the value associated with the specified key.\n\n- **Parameters**: `key` - The key to look up\n- **Returns**: The cached value, or `undefined` if not found\n\n### set(key, value)\n\nStores a value with the specified key.\n\n- **Parameters**: `key` - The key to store the value under, `value` - The value to cache\n- **Returns**: The stored value\n\n### delete(key)\n\nRemoves the value associated with the specified key.\n\n- **Parameters**: `key` - The key to delete\n- **Returns**: `true` if the key was found and deleted, `false` otherwise\n\n### clear()\n\nRemoves all entries from the cache.\n\n- **Parameters**: None\n- **Returns**: `undefined`\n"}}],"model":"qwen/qwen3.5-9b","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5387,"output_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":5279},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d0e62e5c-2e81-456a-907d-b918f16a28ac","uuid":"226d2c9d-6e96-4fd0-8f51-1ed5ca88b173","timestamp":"2026-07-21T04:13:23.262Z"}
